commit 3a4915d436619aef8e73bdd21ea7abafa3e3512e
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 16:17:35 2026 -0400

    feat(forms)(form-engine): migrate volunteer to the engine; harness green for volunteer
    
    Migrate the volunteer form onto the structural Form engine (ADR 0007, Branch 6.4),
    the SECOND form after contact (6.3). Its hand-tuned Effect Schema in `volunteer.tsx`
    (the `Method` discriminator + the per-method cross-field filter + the always-required
    age/location/background/why fields) is deleted and replaced by a data-driven
    `FormDefinition` (`defaultVolunteerForm`) read through `Content.getForm`, rendered by
    `<FormFields>`, and validated by the generic decoder. The route action is the generic
    `formAction({ form, notify, success })` skeleton; the only form-specific part is the
    mailer `notify` (whose body is preserved byte-for-byte, including the always-empty
    `Positions:` line).
    
    The migration is pinned behaviour-preserving by a new equivalence harness
    (`equivalence.volunteer.test.ts`): the pre-migration schema is kept as an ORACLE and a
    full failure-matrix corpus (valid + every invalid variant, per method) runs through
    both oracle and engine, asserting identical decoded output and identical
    emitted-TranslationKey sets (compared on the order-independent client collect-all path)
    plus EN+FR rendered-string parity.
    
    Two deltas are pinned EXPLICITLY (not hidden), each contained to one field:
    - `email` FORMAT validation: the pre-migration volunteer `Email` checked only
      `isMinLength(1)` and accepted a malformed address — a pre-existing drift from
      contact, which DID validate the email shape. The engine's `email` kind validates
      format uniformly (one decoder, `derive-dont-sync`), so volunteer now rejects a
      malformed email with `volunteer.form.email.error` — a deliberate correctness
      tightening (`make-impossible-states-unrepresentable`). The engine is a strict
      superset on `email` only; pinned by `emailFormatTightening`.
    - `positions`: the oracle decoded an absent `positions` to `[]` (a
      `withDecodingDefault`); the never-rendered, never-submitted multi-checkbox had
      dynamic loader-data options (never a closed `OptionList`), so it does not fit the
      closed `FieldKind` set and is dropped (`subtract-before-you-add`). The one decoded-
      default delta is pinned by `decodedDeltaIsPositionsOnly`; `notify` keeps the empty
      `Positions:` line.
    
    The hand-written `volunteer-schema.test.ts` is deleted, its coverage subsumed by the
    equivalence harness. The generic action skeleton's wiring test (`action.test.ts`)
    repoints its empty-graph fixture from `volunteer` to `registration` (the last form with
    a still-empty graph until 6.5).
    
    Gate green: typecheck, lint, build, bun test (523 pass).

